{"cursor":"20662","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"}}\n\nAn 'automobile platform' is a shared set of common design, engineering, and\nproduction efforts, as well as major components over a number of outwardly\ndistinct models and even types of automobiles, often from different, but related\nmarques. | archiveurl= http://web.archive.org/web/20101128200435/http://rmi.org/rmi/Library/T99-\n10_UncommonKnowledge| archivedate= 28 November 2010 | deadurl=\nno}} It is practiced in the automotive industry to reduce the costs\nassociated with the development of products by basing those products on a\nsmaller number of platforms. This further allows companies to create distinct\nmodels from a design perspective on similar underpinnings.\n","linknr":494,"url":"Automobile_platform","recorded":1362579012,"links":40,"instances":["2007","car","international","vehicle"],"pdf":[],"categories":["Automotive technologies","Automobile platforms|"],"headings":["Definition and benefits","Examples","Advantages","Disadvantages","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3f/2007-Toyota-Camry.jpg/220px-2007-Toyota-Camry.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/2007-Lexus-ES350-2.jpg/220px-2007-Lexus-ES350-2.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Ford_Ka_II_front_20100809.jpg/120px-Ford_Ka_II_front_20100809.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/96/2010_Fiat_Panda_4x4_facelift.JPG/120px-2010_Fiat_Panda_4x4_facelift.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/dc/Fiat_Cinquecento.jpg/120px-Fiat_Cinquecento.jpg","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/61/Carro_Vermelho.JPG/120px-Carro_Vermelho.JPG","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/CROMAarr.JPG/220px-CROMAarr.JPG","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a9/Cadillac_BLS_front.JPG/220px-Cadillac_BLS